    "body": "We're running Cython's tests in GraalPy's CI and this test fails on darwin-aarch64 because on that platform `java.Math.sin` (and even `java.StrictMath.sin`)  is one bit off from `libm`'s `sin`. From what I've gathered, these tiny platform differences are normal, so I've modified the test to be a bit (pun intended) more permissive.",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-21T19:47:11Z",
