                "comment_count": 0,
                "committer": {
                    "date": "2026-04-21T14:05:57Z",
                    "email": "michael.simacek@oracle.com",
                    "name": "Michael Simacek"
                },
                "message": "Relax libc_math sin doctest\n\nOn macOS/aarch64, GraalPy hit a failure where libc.sin(4) and math.sin(4) differed by one ULP, which made the doctest fail even though both results were within normal floating-point accuracy. Requiring exact bit identity between two different transcendental implementations is not a stable cross-platform contract.",
